    {
      "page": 2,
      "areas": [
        {
          "name": "Itinerary",
          "color": "#5bba6f",
          "boundingBox": {
            "left": 204,
            "top": 705.9000000000001,
            "width": 352,
            "height": 662.7
          },
          "page": 2,
          "sections": [
            {
              "heading": null,
              "children": [
                {
                  "id": "p2-e42",
                  "text": "Day 1",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontName": "MHPMCN\u002BHelveticaNeue-Medium",
                  "color": "#16549D",
                  "boundingBox": {
                    "left": 212.3,
                    "top": 694.7,
                    "width": 28.9,
                    "height": 7.9
                  },
                  "htmlTag": "",
                  "htmlContainerPath": "",
                  "cssClasses": ""
                },
                {
                  "id": "p2-e43",
                  "text": "We meet at our designated pick up points and transfer by private coach to our allocated London airport for our direct scheduled Turkish Airlines flight to Istanbul. On arrival at Istanbul we are met by our guide who will accompany us on all transfers and included day excursions. We transfer in our private executive coach to the 4* Barcelo Hotel in Istanbul for a four night stay. A welcome dinner is included at our hotel this evening.",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontName": "MHPMDP\u002BHelveticaNeue",
                  "color": "#221F1F",
                  "boundingBox": {
                    "left": 212.3,
                    "top": 683.9,
                    "width": 343.7,
                    "height": 73.1
                  },
                  "htmlTag": "",
                  "htmlContainerPath": "",
                  "cssClasses": ""
                },
                {
                  "id": "p2-e44",
                  "text": "Day 2",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontName": "MHPMCN\u002BHelveticaNeue-Medium",
                  "color": "#16549D",
                  "boundingBox": {
                    "left": 212.3,
                    "top": 602.1,
                    "width": 28.3,
                    "height": 7.9
                  },
                  "htmlTag": "",
                  "htmlContainerPath": "",
                  "cssClasses": ""
                },
                {
                  "id": "p2-e45",
                  "text": "This morning we meet our guide for a tour of the old city. We start by heading to the Sultanahmet district in the heart of historic Old Istanbul and our first visit is to the Blue Mosque. The masterwork of the 17th century Ottoman architect Sedefk\u00E2r Mehmet Aga, with its six minarets and a great cascade of domes, the Mosque is a great feature of the Istanbul skyline. We continue to Topkapi Palace. Home of the Ottoman sultans for nearly 400 years and the heart of the vast Ottoman Empire, Topkapi is today a museum of the old Turkish way of life. During our visit to Topkapi Palace, we see the Fruit Room of Ahmet II, adorned with fruit and floral paintings. This afternoon we visit the Byzantine Church of Hagia Sophia, among the finest architectural works in the world. Its wide, flat dome was a daring engineering feat in the 6th century and architects still marvel at the building\u0027s many innovations. Our day concludes with a visit to the Underground Cistern which was built in the 6th century and supplied water throughout the city during the Byzantine and Ottoman times. Re-discovered in 1545, it was used to water the gardens of Topkapi Palace.",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontName": "MHPMDP\u002BHelveticaNeue",
                  "color": "#221F1F",
                  "boundingBox": {
                    "left": 212.3,
                    "top": 591.4,
                    "width": 346.2,
                    "height": 181.7
                  },
                  "htmlTag": "",
                  "htmlContainerPath": "",
